US-01 · Language Selection · Sprint 1

Choose a coding language before starting a run

As a beginner CS student, I want to choose a programming language before the game starts, so that I can practice syntax that matches what I am currently learning in class.

Acceptance criteria
A language selection menu appears before gameplay begins
At minimum, JavaScript and Python are selectable
All code snippets during the run match the selected language
The chosen language is visibly displayed during gameplay
Notes

Players should feel like the game is helping reinforce familiar syntax rather than forcing them to learn a completely new language mid-run. The selected language should remain consistent throughout the run to avoid confusion.

Dependencies
Snippet generation system must support multiple languages
UI menu system must exist before the run begins
Definition of done

The player can select a language before gameplay, and all generated snippets consistently use that language throughout the session.
